How to build

  Pick the latest deb package from Bitbucket download page (https://bitbucket.org/jsuto/piler/downloads/)
  and use it as the PACKAGE build argument, eg.

  docker build --build-arg PACKAGE=piler_1.3.7-bionic-94c54a0_amd64.deb PACKAGE_DOWNLOAD_SHA256=025bf31155d31c4764c037df29703f85e2e56d66455616a25411928380f49d7c -t woa7/piler .

How to run the image

  Set the PILER_HOST env variable to match your hostname, eg.

  docker run -d --name piler1 -p 25:25 -p 80:80 -e PILER_HOST=archive.yourdomain.com woa7/piler
